#. Tag: title
#: authors.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Authors and History"
msgstr "Avtorji in zgodovina"

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This project was started by Paul Hensgen as one of his University projects. "
"The original name of the application was <application>UML Modeller</"
"application>. Paul did all the development until the end of 2001 when the "
"program reached version 1.0."
msgstr ""
"Ta projekt je začel Paul Hensgen kot enega od svojih univerzitetnih "
"projektov. Prvotno ime aplikacije je bilo <application>UML Modeller</"
"application>. Paul je delal ves razvoj do konca leta 2001, ko je program "
"dosegel različico 1.0."

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Version 1.0 already offered a lot of functionality, but after the project "
"had been reviewed at Paul's University, other developers could join and they "
"started making valuable contributions to <application>UML Modeller</"
"application>, like switching from a binary file format to an &XML; file, "
"support for more types of &UML; Diagrams, Code Generation and Code Import "
"just to name a few."
msgstr ""
"Različica 1.0 je že ponujala veliko funkcionalnosti, toda po tem, ko je bil "
"projekt pregledan na Univerzi Paul's, so se lahko pridružili drugi "
"razvijalci in začeli so dragoceno prispevati k <application>UML Modeller</"
"application>, kot je preklop iz binarne oblike zapisa datoteke v &XML; "
"datoteka, podpora za več vrst &UML; Diagrami, ustvarjanje kode in uvoz kode, "
"če naštejemo samo nekatere."

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Paul had to retire from the development team in Summer 2002 but, as Free and "
"Open Source Software, the program continues to improve and evolve and is "
"being maintained by a group of developers from different parts of the world. "
"In September 2002 the project changed its name from <application>&UML; "
"Modeller</application>, to &umbrello;. There are several reasons for the "
"change of names, the most important ones being that just <quote>uml</quote> "
"&mdash; as it was commonly known &mdash; was a much too generic name and "
"caused problems with some distributions. The other important reason is that "
"the developers think <application>Umbrello</application> is a much cooler "
"name."
msgstr ""
"Paul se je poleti 2002 moral upokojiti iz razvojne ekipe, vendar se program "
"kot prosta in odprtokodna programska oprema še naprej izboljšuje in razvija "
"ter ga vzdržuje skupina razvijalcev iz različnih delov sveta. Septembra 2002 "
"je projekt spremenil ime iz <application>&UML; Modeller</application>, v "
"&umbrello;. Razlogov za spremembo imen je več, najpomembnejši pa je, da samo "
"<quote>uml</quote> &mdash; kot je bilo splošno znano &mdash; je bilo preveč "
"splošno ime in je povzročalo težave z nekaterimi distribucijami. Drugi "
"pomemben razlog je, da razvijalci mislijo, da je <application>Umbrello</"
"application> veliko bolj kul ime."

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The development of &umbrello; as well as discussions as to where the program "
"should head for future versions is open and takes place over the Internet. "
"If you would like to contribute to the project, please do not hesitate to "
"contact the developers. There are many ways in which you can help &umbrello;:"
msgstr ""
"Razvoj &umbrello; pa tudi razprave o tem, kam naj se program usmeri za "
"prihodnje različice, so odprte in potekajo prek interneta. Če želite "
"prispevati k projektu, se obrnite na razvijalce. Obstaja več načinov, kako "
"lahko pomagate &umbrello;:"

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reporting bugs or improvements suggestions"
msgstr "Poročanje o napakah ali predlogi za izboljšave"

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fixing bugs or adding features"
msgstr "Odpravljanje napak ali dodajanje funkcij"

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "Writing good documentation or translating it to other languages"
msgstr "Pisanje dobre dokumentacije ali njeno prevajanje v druge jezike"

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "And of course...coding with us!"
msgstr "In seveda ... kodiranje z nami!"

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As you see, there are many ways in which you can contribute. All of them are "
"very important and everyone is welcome to participate."
msgstr ""
"Kot vidite, obstaja veliko načinov, na katere lahko prispevate. Vsi so zelo "
"pomembni in vsi so dobrodošli k sodelovanju."

#. Tag: para
#: authors.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &umbrello; developers can be reached at <email>umbrello-devel@kde.org</"
"email>."
msgstr ""
"&umbrello; razvijalci so dosegljivi na <email>umbrello-devel@kde.org</email>."
